      <title outputclass="H3_1_9" class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">6.401</ph> Sealed
bidding and competitive proposals.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
         <p otherprops="Body"
            outputclass="Body"
            class="- topic/p "
            id="d400e13">Sealed
bidding and competitive proposals, as described in <ph outputclass="ClauseProvisionXREF" class="- topic/ph ">
               <xref href="FAR-i1111055.dita#i1111055"
                     base="i1111055"
                     outputclass="fm:Parts"
                     class="- topic/xref ">parts  14</xref>
            </ph> and <ph outputclass="ClauseProvisionXREF" class="- topic/ph ">
               <xref href="FAR-i1109360.dita#i1109360"
                     base="i1109360"
                     outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                     class="- topic/xref ">15</xref>
            </ph>,
are both acceptable procedures for use under <ph outputclass="ClauseProvisionXREF" class="- topic/ph ">
               <xref href="FAR-i1120051.dita#i1120051"
                     base="i1120051"
                     outputclass="fm:Subparts"
                     class="- topic/xref ">subparts  6.1</xref>
            </ph>, <ph outputclass="ClauseProvisionXREF" class="- topic/ph ">
               <xref href="FAR-i1119917.dita#i1119917"
                     base="i1119917"
                     outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                     class="- topic/xref ">6.2</xref>
            </ph>;
and, when appropriate, under <ph outputclass="ClauseProvisionXREF" class="- topic/ph ">
               <xref href="FAR-i1119434.dita#i1119434"
                     base="i1119434"
                     outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                     class="- topic/xref ">subpart  6.3</xref>
            </ph>.</p>
         <ol id="d393e46" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li otherprops="abc" outputclass="H5_abc" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d400e50" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Sealed
bids</i>. (See <xref href="FAR-i1111055.dita#i1111055"
                        base="i1111055"
                        outputclass="fm:Part"
                        class="- topic/xref ">part  14</xref> for procedures.) Contracting officers shall solicit sealed
bids if-</p>
               <ol id="d393e62" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d400e66" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                         Time permits the solicitation,
submission, and evaluation of sealed bids;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d400e75" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                         The award will be made on the
basis of price and other price-related factors;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d400e84" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        
                         It is not necessary to conduct
discussions with the responding offerors about their bids; and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d400e93" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph>
                        
                         There is a reasonable expectation
of receiving more than one sealed bid.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li props="Runin"
                otherprops="abcRunin"
                outputclass="H5_abcRunin"
                class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d400e104" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                   Competitive
proposals. (See <xref href="FAR-i1109360.dita#i1109360"
                        base="i1109360"
                        outputclass="fm:Part"
                        class="- topic/xref ">part  15</xref> for procedures.)</p>
               <ol id="d393e113" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li otherprops="123FL" outputclass="H6_123FL" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d400e117" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                         Contracting officers may request
competitive proposals if sealed bids are not appropriate <ph rev="FAC 2019-02 March 27, 2019" class="- topic/ph ">under <?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 6.401 by removing from paragraph (b)(1) “under paragraph (a) above” and adding “under paragraph (a) of this section” in its place.?>paragraph (a) <?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] Technical Amendments?>of this
section</ph>.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li otherprops="123" outputclass="H6_123" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d400e133" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                         Because of differences in areas
such as law, regulations, and business practices, it is generally
necessary to conduct discussions with offerors relative to proposed
contracts to be made and performed outside the United States and
its outlying areas. Competitive proposals will therefore be used
for these contracts unless discussions are not required and the
use of sealed bids is otherwise appropriate.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
